-# Locals: organization, teammate, employee_name (optional)
- organization = local_assigns.fetch(:organization)
- teammate = local_assigns.fetch(:teammate)
- employee_name = local_assigns[:employee_name].presence || teammate.person.casual_name

.alert.alert-light.border.mb-0
  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Goal of this page
  %p.mb-3
    Set how #{employee_name} splits day-to-day Assignment-energy across the organization’s assignments without running a full check-in cycle—while recording a MAAP snapshot for audit.

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Context
  = render 'shared/maap/definition'
  = render 'shared/check_ins/three_step_clarity_flow', organization: organization, teammate: teammate, employee_name: employee_name

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Specifics of this page
  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 This page
  %p.mb-2
    %strong= set_day_to_day_assignments_title
    is a manager/HR tool outside the normal reflect-and-review rhythm (#{set_day_to_day_assignments_subtitle}). Use it to correct tenure forecasts, add assignments, or end active tenure (0% on a row).
  %ul.mb-2
    %li
      %strong Anticipated Energy %
      — live preview on the right energy bar; 0% is omitted from the bar and ends tenure when saved.
    %li
      %strong Save Changes
      — writes tenures and logs the change in MAAP.
    %li
      Assignment links open 1-by-1 check-in context when you need the full reflect flow instead.
  %p.mb-0.text-muted.small
    Prefer the standard flow when possible—use
    = link_to 'Reflect Apart', organization_company_teammate_check_ins_path(organization, teammate)
    and
    = link_to 'Review Together', organization_company_teammate_finalization_path(organization, teammate)
    so both sides reflect before forecasts change.
